        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 1:59AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 159 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Putnam to near Dooling, and moving southwest at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph, frequent lightning and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Ellaville, Oglethorpe, Montezuma, Andersonville, Dooling, Putnam,
Murrays Crossroads, Flint River Wma, Fountainville, La Crosse,
Pennington, Draneville, Andersonville National Historic, Friendship,
Clearview, Bumphead, Church Hill, and Walls Crossing.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
